      143.85,
      306.77,
      383.85,
      329.39
    ],
    "text": "1.This Act may be cited as the People's Bank(Amendment) Act, No. 16 of 2019.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times",
      "Times,Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      143.85,
      340.73,
      383.92,
      374.63
    ],
    "text": "2.Section 12 of the People's Bank Act, No. 29 of 1961(hereinafter referred to as the principal enactment) is herebyrepealed and the following section is substituted therefor:-",
    "fonts": [
      "Times",
      "Times,Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      197.85,
      385.85,
      383.87,
      419.87
    ],
    "text": "12. (1) The authorised capital of the Bankshall be rupees fifty billion divided into onebillion shares of rupees fifty each.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      197.85,
      431.09,
      383.88,
      487.67
    ],
    "text": "(2) (a) The Minister may, in the interest ofthe national economy, where he deems itnecessary, determine from time to time the paid-up capital of the Bank, by Order published inthe Gezette.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times",
      "Times,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      197.85,
      498.89,
      383.86,
      544.07
    ],
    "text": "(b) No Order made by the Minister underthis section shall take effect unless such Orderis approved by Parliament within ninety daysfrom the date of its publication in the Gazette..",
    "fonts": [
      "Times",
      "Times,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      143.85,
      555.41,
      383.88,
      578.03
    ],
    "text": "3.Section 20 of the principal enactment is herebyrepealed and the following section is substituted therefor:-",
    "fonts": [
      "Times",
      "Times,Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.0
